## 10. Immediate Refactoring Recommendations

Before proceeding to build future modules, you must apply the following structural refactorings:

### 1. Implement API Transaction Wrappers
Refactor all multi-write API endpoints to run inside Drizzle transaction blocks. Example for `/api/admin/timetable/route.ts`:
```typescript
await db.transaction(async (tx) => {
  await tx.update(timetableEntries).set({ isActive: false }).where(...);
  if (inserts.length > 0) {
    await tx.insert(timetableEntries).values(inserts);
  }
  if (division.publishStatus === "published") {
    await tx.update(divisions).set({ publishStatus: "draft" }).where(...);
  }
});
```

### 2. Optimize Auth Downstream Handlers
Update API routes to trust and consume the headers injected by `middleware.ts` (`x-user-id`, `x-user-roles`, `x-faculty-code`, `x-active-role`), completely bypassing the redundant `verifyToken` call:
```typescript
export async function POST(req: NextRequest) {
  const userId = req.headers.get("x-user-id");
  const roles = JSON.parse(req.headers.get("x-user-roles") || "[]");
  if (!userId) return err("Unauthorized", 401);
  // Proceed with business logic...
}
```

### 3. Payload Duplicate Checks in Student Upload
Refactor student bulk onboarding to filter out internal duplicates in the CSV payload before writing to the database:
```typescript
const uniqueIncomingIds = Array.from(new Set(studentRows.map((s) => s.id)));
const uniqueIncomingEmails = Array.from(new Set(studentRows.map((s) => s.email)));
// Proceed with DB check against unique arrays...
```

